WEREWOLF

Werewolves are MDC lycanthropes, supernatural shapeshifters cursed or
blessed (depending on perspective) with the ability to transform between
human and wolf-hybrid forms.  On Rifts Earth, werewolf packs operate across
the wilderness, generally avoiding the Coalition and preying on those who
wander too far from the safety of towns.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 3-18   ME: 3-18   MA: 3-18   PS: 12-32 (Supernatural)
  PP: 7-22   PE: 10-30  PB: 3-18   Spd: 14-34

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 3d6 x10 + 30 (approx 60-210 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Rapid regeneration: 2d6 MDC per melee round
  - Enhanced smell and hearing
  - Exceptional Spd (very fast in humanoid and wolf form)
  - Lycanthropic immunity to non-silver weapons

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Vulnerable to silver: double damage from silver weapons
  - Uncontrolled transformation risk under emotional stress
  - Lycanthropy can be passed to victims

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

See also: werebear, weretiger, secondary_vampire, races
